        <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Hd1e108">Rubrica 12</head>
        <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De facilitate et difficultate</head>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e114">
          <lb ed="#V" n="13"/>
          ¶ De facilitate et difficultate. Rubrica. 12
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e119">
          
          <lb ed="#V" n="14"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Rd1e116">PSalmista psalmus. 9.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e123">Cuius
            <lb ed="#V" n="15"/>
            maledictio<lb ed="#V" n="16" break="no"/>ne os plenum est: et amaritudine: sub
            <lb ed="#V" n="17"/>lingua eius labor et dolor.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e133">
          <lb ed="#V" n="18"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Rd1e132">Isaias propheta. c. 26</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e137">Semita iusti recta est
            <lb ed="#V" n="19"/>rectus callis iusti ad ambulandum</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e144">
          <lb ed="#V" n="20"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Rd1e145">Aristoteles ethicorum. li. 2. c. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e148">Circa 
            diffici<lb ed="#V" n="21" break="no"/>lius semper et ars fit et virtus.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e154"> /
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Rd1e155">Idem de 
            me<lb ed="#V" n="22" break="no"/>moria et reminiscentia:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e156">Sunt magis 
              remini<lb ed="#V" n="23" break="no"/>scibiliora quecumque ordinationem habent.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e164"> /
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Rd1e168">Idem
            <lb ed="#V" n="24"/>iconomicorum libro i. in fi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e166">Oportet vnumquodque
              <lb ed="#V" n="25"/>in loco suo poni. Sic enim paratum existens
              <lb ed="#V" n="26"/>non queretur.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e176"> /
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Rd1e183">Idem rethoricorum libro i. c. 10.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e178">
            Faci<lb ed="#V" n="27" break="no"/>lia sunt quecumque fiunt sine tristitia: vel in 
            mo<lb ed="#V" n="28" break="no"/>dico tempore. Difficile enim determinantur aut
            <lb ed="#V" n="29"/>tristitia aut multitudine temporis.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e188"> /
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Rd1e197">Idem 
            elemen<lb ed="#V" n="30" break="no"/>torum libro i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e190">Difficile est simul multa conspicere.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e196">
          <lb ed="#V" n="31"/>
          / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Rd1e210">Li. 2. et fi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e200">Prouidere quidem difficile est: per
            <lb ed="#V" n="32"/>vacationem autem videre facile. Inuento 
            faci<lb ed="#V" n="33" break="no"/>le est addere.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e209">
          <lb ed="#V" n="34"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Rd1e225">Terentius in heautontumerumenos. c. 17</ref>
          <lb ed="#V" n="35"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e213">Nulla res est tanta facilis: quin difficilis fiet
            <lb ed="#V" n="36"/>quam inuitus facias.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e221">
          <lb ed="#V" n="37"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Rd1e239">Salustius in catalinario:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e225">Que quisque 
            fa<lb ed="#V" n="38" break="no"/>cilia factu putat equo animo accipit.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e231">
          <lb ed="#V" n="39"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Rd1e251">Tullius retho. artis vereris li. 2. c. 12.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e235">
            Fa<lb ed="#V" n="40" break="no"/>cile fieri id dicimus quod sine magno aut
            <lb ed="#V" n="41"/>sine vllo labore sumptu molestia quam breuis
            <lb ed="#V" n="42"/>simo tempore confici potest: difficile autem
            <lb ed="#V" n="43"/>fieri quod quamquam laboris sumptus molestie 
            lon<lb ed="#V" n="44" break="no"/>gitudinis indiget: atque omnes: aut plurimas
            <lb ed="#V" n="45"/>aut maximas causas habet difficultatis: tantum <!--70.xml-->
            <cb ed="#V" n="b"/>
            <lb ed="#V" n="46"/>his susceptis difficultatibus compleri atque
            <lb ed="#V" n="47"/>ad exitum perduci potest.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e260"> /
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Rd1e280">Idem de orato
            <lb ed="#V" n="48"/>re li. 3. et fi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e262">Facilius est apta dissoluere quam
              <lb ed="#V" n="49"/>dissipata connectere.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e270"> /
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Rd1e293">Idem super timeum 
            pla<lb ed="#V" n="50" break="no"/>tonis de essentina mundi:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e272">Difficillimum est in
              <lb ed="#V" n="51"/>omni conquisitione rationis exordium.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e280">
          <lb ed="#V" n="52"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Rd1e308">Ouidius epistolarum. 12. c.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e284">Ultimus est
            <lb ed="#V" n="53"/>aliqua decipere arte labor.<ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Rd1e314">Epistola. 16.</ref>
            <lb ed="#V" n="54"/>Difficilem culpe suspicor esse viam.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e293"> /
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Rd1e323">De 
            tri<lb ed="#V" n="55" break="no"/>stibus libro. 3. c. 11.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e295">In causa facili cui ius
              <lb ed="#V" n="56"/>licet esse dissertur. Et minime vires 
              frange<lb ed="#V" n="57" break="no"/>re quassa valent.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e305">
          <lb ed="#V" n="58"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Rd1e340">Seneca de ira libro. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e309">Nihil est difficile
            <lb ed="#V" n="59"/>et arduum quod non humana mens vincat: et
            <lb ed="#V" n="60"/>in familiaritatem perducat assidua 
            medita<lb ed="#V" n="61" break="no"/>tio.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e319"> /
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Rd1e354">Idem de consolatione ad helbiam:</ref>
          <lb ed="#V" n="62"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e321">Nihil homini natura quod necessarium 
            facie<lb ed="#V" n="63" break="no"/>bat fecit operosum.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e329">
          <lb ed="#V" n="64"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Rd1e368">Lex aucten. ti. de monachis.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e333">§. scimus. Non <!--add '§' to ref tag?-->
            <lb ed="#V" n="65"/>facilis est vite mutatio sed cum magno 
            ani<lb ed="#V" n="66" break="no"/>mi fit labore.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e341">
          <lb ed="#V" n="67"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Rd1e384">Uegecius de re militari li. i. c. 20.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e345">
            Quotti<lb ed="#V" n="68" break="no"/>dianus vsus non laborat: etsi onerosa 
            gesta<lb ed="#V" n="69" break="no"/>uerit.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e353"> /
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Rd1e396">Libro. 3 ti. 17.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e355">Omne opus 
            diffi<lb ed="#V" n="70" break="no"/>cile videtur antequam tentes.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e362">
          <lb ed="#V" n="71"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Rd1e409">Augustinus in epigrama. prosperi. 65.
            <lb ed="#V" n="72"/>emp.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e366">Difficilia et laboriosa sunt figmenta
              <lb ed="#V" n="73"/>mendacii: qui autem vult verum dicere: non
              <lb ed="#V" n="74"/>laborat.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e376">
          <lb ed="#V" n="75"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Rd1e426">Gualterius de castellione alexandreidos
            <lb ed="#V" n="76"/>8. libro.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e380">O quam difficile visu sors prouehit
              <lb ed="#V" n="77"/>actus Lubrica mortales: et quos 
              ascende<lb ed="#V" n="78" break="no"/>re fecit: Quam facile euereit: magno fortuna
              <lb ed="#V" n="79"/>labore.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e392">
          <lb ed="#V" n="80"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Rd1e445">Mattheus vindocinensis in poetria: par.
            <lb ed="#V" n="81"/>2. et fi. cap. 8.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e396">Leuius est inferre vulnera quam
              <lb ed="#V" n="82"/>sanare.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e404">
          <lb ed="#V" n="83"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Rd1e460">Ganfred. in poetria. c. 30.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e408">Facti grauitas
            <lb ed="#V" n="84"/>cuicumque volenti. Est leuis et leuitas animo
            <lb ed="#V" n="85"/>cuicumque rebelli Est grauis.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e416">
          <lb ed="#V" n="86"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Rd1e474">Ricardus iudex venusinus:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e420">Est labor in 
            la<lb ed="#V" n="87" break="no"/>biis mendacia composituris. Uera 
            locutu<lb ed="#V" n="88" break="no"/>ris non labor vllus inest.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-d1e428">
          <lb ed="#V" n="89"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Rd1e488">Montanarius in luna cleri:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d16352-Qd1e432">Leuiter fit
            <lb ed="#V" n="90"/>quicquid amatur. <!--71.xml-->
          </quote>
        </p>
      </div>
